'''Rha Woong-bae''' (born 24 July 1934) is the Chairman of the Hanbit Forum. He was also the former Finance and Economy Minister and deputy Prime Minister of the [[Republic of Korea]] under President [[Kim Dae-jung]].<ref>''Korea Newsreview'', Volume 25, p. 12</ref><ref>''Global Banking and Financial Policy Review'', 1997, Euromoney Publications PLC., p. 70</ref> He served as Trade and Industry Minister in the 1980s.<ref>"Baldrige to Ask Seoul to Hike Currency Value", ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'', April 18, 1987, p. 20</ref>

He holds a [[PhD]] (1968) from the [[Haas School of Business]] at the [[University of California, Berkeley]].

